Manufacturer is O.F. Mossberg & Sons of New Haven, CT. Construction on this 930 is steel barrel, bolt, and parts, built into a light weight alloy receiver with matching alloy trigger housing. Type is dual system self regulating gas operated semi-automatic, made to specs for the zealous Carolina security contractor whose name it bears. Chambering is for 12 gauge shells, 2 3/4 inch and 3 inch magnums interchangeably. Capacity with extended 

Choate factory installed tube is 7 + 1 + a ghost round as seen here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KpyNoCnO4B4 6 + 1 on 3 inch. We have added an extension tube clamp, since the 930 lug does not have a detent ball. Operators should keep the clamp tight. Barrel is 18 1/2 inch Cylinder Bore, .725 muzzle diameter. 

Since the 930 is not back bored, it will handle rifled slugs and sabots just fine. Sight system is factory issue, low profile XS brand windage and elevation adjustable, removable aperture or Ghost Ring rear sight integral to its 10 slot Picatinny Rail. Receiver on the 930 is contoured like the Model 500 and 835 shotguns, for a Weaver #88 or 417 four screw base. Front sight is raised, white bar blade type. Operating handle is oversize knurled steel. Safety is classic Mossberg top tang style; and the .250 smooth face blue steel trigger pulls at 5 pound vicinity with minimal felt creep. Length of pull is 14 inches from the trigger face to the end of the 1 inch black factory recoil pad. Weight empty is 7 1/2 pounds, with center of gravity at the operating handle.
